  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. The line in slope-intercept form is <i>y</i> = <i>mx</i> + <i>b</i> with <i>m</i> = 7 and <i>b</i> = &minus;2, giving <i>y</i> = 7<i>x</i> &minus; 2.</p><p>Choices B, C, and D confuse the slope with the <i>y</i>-intercept or use the wrong sign for the <i>y</i>-intercept.</p>",
